# Function to generate and display pie chart
generate_pie_chart <- function(data, title, output_png) {
  # Summarize abundance
  abundance_summary <- data %>%
    group_by(Genus) %>%
    summarize(TotalAbundance = sum(n, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
    arrange(desc(TotalAbundance))

  # Identify top 19 taxa and group the rest as "Others"
  top_taxa <- abundance_summary$Genus[1:19]
  pie_data <- abundance_summary %>%
    mutate(Taxa_Genus = ifelse(Genus %in% top_taxa, Genus, "Others")) %>%
    group_by(Taxa_Genus) %>%
    summarize(TotalAbundance = sum(TotalAbundance, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
    mutate(Percentage = TotalAbundance / sum(TotalAbundance) * 100)

  # Add percentages to legend labels
  pie_data <- pie_data %>%
    mutate(Taxa_Genus = paste0(Taxa_Genus, " (", round(Percentage, 1), "%)"))

  # Generate distinct colors for the chart (20 total categories)
distinct_colors <- brewer.pal(n = 11, name = "Paired")  # Paired palette with 11 colors
distinct_colors <- c(distinct_colors, brewer.pal(n = 7, name = "Dark2"), brewer.pal(n = 3, name = "Set3"))


  # Create the pie chart
  pie_chart <- ggplot(pie_data, aes(x = "", y = TotalAbundance, fill = Taxa_Genus)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 1) +
    coord_polar(theta = "y") +
    labs(title = title, fill = "Taxa") +
    theme_void() +
    theme(
      legend.position = "bottom", # Move legend to the bottom
      legend.key.size = unit(0.4, "cm"), # Adjust legend key size
      legend.text = element_text(size = 5), # Adjust legend text size
      plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, size = 10), # Larger title
      plot.margin = margin(t = 10, r = 0, b = 10, l = 10) # Adjust margins
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = distinct_colors)

  # Save as PNG with larger dimensions
  png(output_png, width = 12, height = 8, units = "in", res = 600)
  print(pie_chart)
  dev.off()

  # Print to HTML
  print(pie_chart)
}

# Generate pie charts for plant and animal unique taxa
generate_pie_chart(unique_plant_data, "Unique Plant Taxa", "Unique_Plant_Taxa_Piechart.png")

  # Data preparation
  if (!file.exists("Protein_filt.rds")) {
    Protein <- qza_to_phyloseq(
      features = "TWO_table.qza",
      tree = "Protein_rooted-tree.qza",
      taxonomy = "PROTEIN_NEW_taxonomy.qza",
      metadata = "FINAL_Metadata.tsv"
    )

    # Ensure OTU table is accessible
    if (!inherits(Protein, "phyloseq")) {
      stop("Protein object is not a valid phyloseq object.")
    }

    Protein_filt <- prune_taxa(taxa_sums(Protein) > 1, Protein)
    saveRDS(Protein_filt, "Protein_filt.rds")
    cat("Data preparation complete. Protein_filt saved as 'Protein_filt.rds'.\n")
  } else {
    Protein_filt <- readRDS("Protein_filt.rds")
    cat("Protein_filt loaded from 'Protein_filt.rds'.\n")
  }

  # Preprocess the phyloseq object
  pseq <- Protein_filt %>%
    tax_filter(min_prevalence = 1) %>%
    tax_fix(unknowns = c("uncultured"))

  # Create genus composition bar plot
  genus_plot <- pseq %>%
    ps_select(Protein_source, Protein_level) %>%
    phyloseq::merge_samples(group = "Protein_source") %>%
    comp_barplot(
      tax_level = "Genus",
      n_taxa = 19,
      bar_width = 0.8,
      position = position_dodge(width = 0.6),
      transform = function(x) x * 100
    ) +
    labs(
      x = "Protein Source",
      y = "Relative Abundance (%)"
    ) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(
      axis.text.x = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      axis.text.y = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      axis.title.x = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14),
      axis.title.y = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14),
      legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
      legend.title = element_text(face = "bold")

# Save or load alpha diversity plot
alpha_div_plot_rds <- "alpha_div_plot.rds"
if (!file.exists(alpha_div_plot_rds)) {
  # Calculate alpha diversity
  alpha_diversity <- estimate_richness(Protein_filt, measures = c("Shannon", "Observed"))
  alpha_diversity$SequencingDepth <- sample_sums(Protein_filt)
  
  # Spearman correlation
  cor_result <- cor.test(alpha_diversity$SequencingDepth, alpha_diversity$Shannon, method = "spearman")
  cor_rho <- round(cor_result$estimate, 3)
  cor_pval <- signif(cor_result$p.value, 3)
  
  # Generate scatter plot
  alpha_div_plot <- ggplot(alpha_diversity, aes(x = SequencingDepth, y = Shannon)) +
    geom_point(size = 3, color = "steelblue") +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
    labs(
      title = "Sequencing Depth vs Microbial Diversity",
      x = "Sequencing Depth (Total Reads)",
      y = "Shannon Diversity Index"
    ) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14, hjust = 0.5),
      axis.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      axis.text = element_text(size = 10)
    ) +
    annotate("text", x = max(alpha_diversity$SequencingDepth) * 0.7,
             y = max(alpha_diversity$Shannon) * 0.95,
             label = paste0("Spearman's rho = ", cor_rho, "\nP-value = ", cor_pval),
             color = "red", size = 5, hjust = 0)
  
  # Save the plot object
  saveRDS(alpha_div_plot, alpha_div_plot_rds)
  cat("Alpha diversity plot saved.\n")
} else {
  # Load the plot object
  alpha_div_plot <- readRDS(alpha_div_plot_rds)
  cat("Alpha diversity plot loaded.\n")
}

# Save or load GLMM model results
glmm_results_rds <- "glmm_results.rds"
if (!file.exists(glmm_results_rds)) {
  # Extract metadata and alpha diversity
  alpha_div <- estimate_richness(Protein_filt, measures = "Shannon")
  metadata <- data.frame(sample_data(Protein_filt))
  alpha_div_df <- cbind(alpha_div, metadata)
  
  # Fit GLMM models
  model1 <- lmer(Shannon ~ Protein_source + (1 | Isolation_source), data = alpha_div_df)
  model2 <- lmer(Shannon ~ Protein_source + Protein_level + Country + (1 | Isolation_source), data = alpha_div_df)
  model3 <- lmer(Shannon ~ Protein_source + Protein_level + Country + Isolation_source + (1 | Isolation_source), data = alpha_div_df)
  # Save results
  glmm_results <- list(model1 = model1, model2 = model2, model3 = model3)
  saveRDS(glmm_results, glmm_results_rds)
  cat("GLMM results saved.\n")
} else {
  # Load results
  glmm_results <- readRDS(glmm_results_rds)
  cat("GLMM results loaded.\n")
}
## GLMM results loaded.
# Extract models
model1 <- glmm_results$model1
model2 <- glmm_results$model2
model3 <- glmm_results$model3

# Compare models using AIC
aic_results <- AIC(model1, model2, model3)
print(aic_results)

# Perform PCoA
ProteinPCA_aitchison <- cmdscale(aitchison_dist, k = 2, eig = TRUE)

# Calculate Variance Explained

variance_explained <- positive_eigenvalues / sum(positive_eigenvalues) * 100

  otu_clr <- as.matrix(otu_table(Protein_filt_clr))
  aitchison_dist <- dist(t(otu_clr), method = "euclidean")

  aitchison_dist <- readRDS(aitchison_dist_rds)
}

# Step 3: Run ANOSIM (Re-use or Load Precomputed Results)
if (!file.exists(anosim_res_rds)) {
  metadata <- as(sample_data(Protein_filt), "data.frame")
  grouping_var <- metadata$Protein_source
  anosim_res <- anosim(aitchison_dist, grouping_var, permutations = 999)
  saveRDS(anosim_res, anosim_res_rds)
} else {
  anosim_res <- readRDS(anosim_res_rds)
}

# Extract ANOSIM Results
R_value <- round(anosim_res$statistic, 3)
p_value <- signif(anosim_res$signif, 3)

# Step 4: Create or Load ANOSIM Plot
if (!file.exists(anosim_plot_rds)) {
  # Convert Distance Matrix to Long Format
  dissimilarity_df <- as.data.frame(as.table(as.matrix(aitchison_dist)))
  colnames(dissimilarity_df) <- c("Sample1", "Sample2", "Distance")
  
  # Add grouping information
  metadata <- as(sample_data(Protein_filt), "data.frame")
  dissimilarity_df$Group1 <- metadata$Protein_source[match(dissimilarity_df$Sample1, rownames(metadata))]
  dissimilarity_df$Group2 <- metadata$Protein_source[match(dissimilarity_df$Sample2, rownames(metadata))]
  
  # Define Within-Group and Between-Group comparisons
  dissimilarity_df$Type <- ifelse(dissimilarity_df$Group1 == dissimilarity_df$Group2, 
                                  paste0("Within-", dissimilarity_df$Group1), 
                                  "Between-Groups")
  
  # Remove duplicates and self-comparisons
  dissimilarity_df <- dissimilarity_df[dissimilarity_df$Sample1 != dissimilarity_df$Sample2, ]
  
  # Normalize Distances Between 0 and 1
  dissimilarity_df$Normalized_Distance <- scales::rescale(dissimilarity_df$Distance, to = c(0, 1))
  
  # Create ANOSIM Plot
  anosim_plot <- ggplot(dissimilarity_df, aes(x = Type, y = Normalized_Distance, fill = Type)) +
    geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7, outlier.shape = NA) +
    stat_summary(fun = "median", geom = "point", size = 4, color = "black", shape = 18) +
    stat_summary(fun = "median", geom = "text", aes(label = round(..y.., 3)), vjust = -1.0, size = 3.5) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
    annotate("text", x = 2, y = 0.95, label = paste0("ANOSIM: R = ", R_value, ", p = ", p_value), size = 4) +
    labs(
      x = "Group Comparison",
      y = "Aitchison Dissimilarity Distance"
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("Within-Plant" = "blue", "Within-Animal" = "red", "Between-Groups" = "purple")) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(
      axis.title.x = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
      axis.title.y = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
      legend.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 12),
      axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10)
    )
  
  # Save ANOSIM Plot
  saveRDS(anosim_plot, anosim_plot_rds)
} else {
  anosim_plot <- readRDS(anosim_plot_rds)
}

# Display the Plot
print(anosim_plot)

6. RANDOM FOREST MODEL PREDICTION

if (!file.exists("random_forest_model.rds") || !file.exists("random_forest_importance.csv")) {
  # Load required libraries silently
  libraries <- c("randomForest", "phyloseq", "ggplot2", "dplyr", "caret")
  invisible(lapply(libraries, function(pkg) suppressMessages(suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(pkg, character.only = TRUE)))))

  # Make Training Dataset
  predict <- t(otu_table(Protein_filt))
  res <- sample_data(Protein_filt)$Protein_source
  Protein_rf <- data.frame(res, predict)
  
  # Train Random Forest model
  set.seed(2000)
  proteinclass <- randomForest(res ~ ., data = Protein_rf, ntree = 1000, importance = TRUE)
  
  # Save model
  saveRDS(proteinclass, "random_forest_model.rds")
  cat("Random Forest model saved as 'random_forest_model.rds'.\n")
  
  # Extract importance scores
  impcl <- randomForest::importance(proteinclass)
  impcl_df <- data.frame(OTUID = rownames(impcl), impcl)
  impcl_df$OTUID <- gsub("X", "", impcl_df$OTUID)  # Remove 'X' prefix
  
  # Merge with taxonomic information
  otu_df <- as.data.frame(tax_table(Protein_filt))
  otu_df$OTUID <- rownames(otu_df)
  imp_merged <- merge(impcl_df, otu_df, by = "OTUID") %>%
    filter(MeanDecreaseAccuracy > 0) %>%
    arrange(desc(MeanDecreaseAccuracy)) %>%
    head(10)
  
  # Save importance data
  write.csv(imp_merged, "random_forest_importance.csv", row.names = FALSE)
  cat("Feature importance saved as 'random_forest_importance.csv'.\n")
} else {
  # Load saved model and importance data
  suppressMessages(library(randomForest))  # Suppress output when loading the library
  proteinclass <- readRDS("random_forest_model.rds")
  imp_merged <- read.csv("random_forest_importance.csv")
  cat("Random Forest model and importance data loaded from saved files.\n")
}

4. Generate Test Data Confusion Matrix and Plot

if (!file.exists("confusion_matrix_plot.rds")) {
  # Make predictions
  predictions <- predict(typeclassval, newdata = testprot)$class
  true_labels <- testprot$typeres
  conf_table <- table(Predicted = predictions, Actual = true_labels)

  # Create data frame for plotting
  conf_df <- as.data.frame(conf_table)
  conf_df$Accuracy <- (conf_df$Freq / sum(conf_table)) * 100
  conf_df$Label <- paste0(conf_df$Freq, " (", round(conf_df$Accuracy, 1), "%)")

  # Generate confusion matrix plot
  library(ggplot2)
  confusion_plot <- ggplot(data = conf_df, aes(x = Predicted, y = Actual, fill = Freq)) +
    geom_tile(color = "white") +
    geom_text(aes(label = Label), color = "black") +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "blue") +
    labs(title = "Test Data Confusion Matrix", x = "Predicted", y = "Actual", fill = "Frequency") +
    theme_minimal()

  # Save plot
  saveRDS(confusion_plot, "confusion_matrix_plot.rds")
  cat("Confusion matrix plot saved as 'confusion_matrix_plot.rds'.\n")
  print(confusion_plot)
} else {
  # Load and display the plot
  confusion_plot <- readRDS("confusion_matrix_plot.rds")
  print(confusion_plot)

# Filter and save Protein.genera for future use
if (!file.exists("filtered_protein_genera.rds")) {
  # Ensure imp_merged and Protein_filt exist
  if (!exists("imp_merged") || !exists("Protein_filt")) {
    stop("Required objects 'imp_merged' or 'Protein_filt' are missing.")
  }

  # Get the top genera
  top_genera <- unique(imp_merged$Genus)  # Assuming the top 10 are already selected

  # Filter and process Protein_genera
  Protein_genera <- Protein_filt %>%
    tax_glom(taxrank = "Genus") %>%                     # Agglomerate at genus level
    transform_sample_counts(function(x) { x / sum(x) }) %>%  # Transform to relative abundance
    psmelt() %>%                                         # Melt into long format
    dplyr::arrange(Phylum)                              # Sort by Phylum

  # Filter Protein_genera to include only the top 10 taxa
  Protein_genera_filtered <- Protein_genera %>%
    filter(Genus %in% top_genera)

  # Save the filtered Protein_genera
  saveRDS(Protein_genera_filtered, "filtered_protein_genera.rds")
  cat("Filtered protein genera saved as 'filtered_protein_genera.rds'.\n")
} else {
  # Load saved filtered data
  Protein_genera_filtered <- readRDS("filtered_protein_genera.rds")
  cat("Filtered protein genera loaded from 'filtered_protein_genera.rds'.\n")
}
## Filtered protein genera loaded from 'filtered_protein_genera.rds'.
# Create and save the log10 abundance box plot
if (!file.exists("log10_abundance_boxplot.rds")) {
  # Ensure ggpubr is loaded
  suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(ggpubr))

  # Ensure Protein_source column exists
  if (!"Protein_source" %in% colnames(Protein_genera_filtered)) {
    stop("The 'Protein_source' column is missing in the filtered data.")
  }

  # Preprocess data: Remove zero or negative values before log transformation
  plot_data <- Protein_genera_filtered %>%
    filter(Protein_source %in% c("Plant", "Animal")) %>%
    filter(Abundance > 0)  # Remove rows with zero or negative abundance values

  # Create the box plot
  boxplot_data <- plot_data %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Protein_source, y = Abundance, fill = Protein_source)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    scale_y_log10() +
    facet_wrap(~Genus, scales = "free_y", nrow = 2) +
    stat_compare_means(comparisons = list(c("Plant", "Animal")), label = 'p.signif') +
    labs(x = "", y = "Log10 Abundance", fill = "Protein Source") +
    theme_classic2() +

6 Random Forest Randomization

if (!file.exists("random_forest_randomization_plot.rds")) {
  # Load required libraries and data
  library(phyloseq)
  library(ggplot2)
  library(caret)

  if (!exists("typeres") || !exists("rfprot") || !exists("typeclassval")) {
    if (file.exists("Protein_filt.rds")) {
      Protein_filt <- readRDS("Protein_filt.rds")
      
      # Ensure `otu_table` and `sample_data` functions are recognized
      if (!inherits(Protein_filt, "phyloseq")) {
        stop("Protein_filt is not a valid phyloseq object.")
      }
      
      predictprotein <- t(otu_table(Protein_filt))
      typeres <- sample_data(Protein_filt)$Protein_source
      rfprot <- data.frame(typeres, predictprotein)
    } else {
      stop("Required file 'Protein_filt.rds' not found.")
    }

    if (file.exists("random_forest_model.rds")) {
      typeclassval <- readRDS("random_forest_model.rds")
    } else {
      stop("Random Forest model ('random_forest_model.rds') not found.")
    }
  }

  # Split data into training and test sets
  set.seed(28)
  trainIndex <- createDataPartition(typeres, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
  train_set <- rfprot[trainIndex, ]
  test_set <- rfprot[-trainIndex, ]

  # Generate random labels for the test set
  set.seed(42)
  num_test_samples <- nrow(test_set)
  random_labels <- sample(c(1, 2), num_test_samples, replace = TRUE)
  test_set$random_labels <- random_labels

  # Make predictions on the test set
  random_predictions <- predict(typeclassval, newdata = test_set)$class

  # Create confusion matrix
  conf_matrix <- table(Predicted = random_predictions, Actual = test_set$random_labels)
  cat("Confusion matrix for random labels:\n")
  print(conf_matrix)

  # Convert confusion matrix to a data frame
  conf_df <- as.data.frame(conf_matrix)
  conf_df$Accuracy <- (conf_df$Freq / sum(conf_matrix)) * 100
  conf_df$Label <- paste0(conf_df$Freq, " (", round(conf_df$Accuracy, 1), "%)")

  # Plot confusion matrix
  conf_matrix_plot <- ggplot(conf_df, aes(x = Predicted, y = Actual, fill = Freq)) +
    geom_tile(color = "white") +
    geom_text(aes(label = Label), color = "black", size = 5) +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "blue") +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(title = "Randomized Data Confusion Matrix", x = "Predicted", y = "Actual") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  # Save the plot object
  saveRDS(conf_matrix_plot, "random_forest_randomization_plot.rds")
  print(conf_matrix_plot)
} else {
  # Load and display the saved plot
  conf_matrix_plot <- readRDS("random_forest_randomization_plot.rds")
  print(conf_matrix_plot)
}

    p_mat <- matrix(NA, nrow = ncol(mat1), ncol = ncol(mat2))
    for (i in 1:ncol(mat1)) {
      for (j in 1:ncol(mat2)) {
        test <- cor.test(mat1[, i], mat2[, j], method = method)

# Custom function to calculate p-values for correlations
cor.mtest <- function(mat1, mat2, method = "spearman") {
  p_mat <- matrix(NA, nrow = ncol(mat1), ncol = ncol(mat2))
  for (i in 1:ncol(mat1)) {
    for (j in 1:ncol(mat2)) {
      test <- cor.test(mat1[, i], mat2[, j], method = method)
      p_mat[i, j] <- test$p.value
    }
  }
  return(list(p = p_mat))
}
# File paths for correlation and p-values

p_values_file <- "p_values_significant.rds"

if (!file.exists(cor_matrix_file) || !file.exists(p_values_file)) {
  # Calculate correlation matrix
  cor_matrix <- cor(t(taxa_abundance), flux_metadata, method = "spearman")
  
  # Calculate p-values
  p_values <- cor.mtest(t(taxa_abundance), flux_metadata, method = "spearman")$p
  
  # Identify significant taxa
  significant_taxa <- apply(p_values, 1, function(row) any(row < 0.05))
  
  # Subset matrices for significant taxa
  cor_matrix_significant <- cor_matrix[significant_taxa, ]
  p_values_significant <- p_values[significant_taxa, ]
  
  # Save results
  saveRDS(cor_matrix_significant, cor_matrix_file)
  saveRDS(p_values_significant, p_values_file)
  cat("Significant correlation matrix and p-values saved.\n")
} else {

# File paths for saving
taxonomy_file <- "taxonomy_table.rds"
otu_to_genus_file <- "otu_to_genus.rds"

if (!file.exists(taxonomy_file) || !file.exists(otu_to_genus_file)) {
  # Extract taxonomy and prepare
  taxonomy <- as.data.frame(tax_table(Protein_filt))  # Replace `Protein` with your phyloseq object
  taxonomy <- taxonomy %>%
    tibble::rownames_to_column(var = "OTU") %>%
    tidyr::replace_na(list(
      Kingdom = "Unassigned", Phylum = "Unassigned", Class = "Unassigned",
      Order = "Unassigned", Family = "Unassigned", Genus = "Unassigned",
      Species = "Unassigned"
    ))
  otu_to_genus <- taxonomy[, c("OTU", "Genus")]
  
  # Save outputs
  saveRDS(taxonomy, taxonomy_file)
  saveRDS(otu_to_genus, otu_to_genus_file)
  cat("Saved taxonomy and OTU-to-Genus mapping.\n")
} else {
  taxonomy <- readRDS(taxonomy_file)
  otu_to_genus <- readRDS(otu_to_genus_file)
  cat("Loaded taxonomy and OTU-to-Genus mapping from files.\n")
}
## Loaded taxonomy and OTU-to-Genus mapping from files.
# Define file paths for saving results
updated_cor_matrix_file <- "updated_cor_matrix_top50.rds"
updated_significant_markers_file <- "updated_significant_markers_top50.rds"

if (!file.exists(updated_cor_matrix_file) || !file.exists(updated_significant_markers_file)) {
  # Ensure the taxonomy table contains the correct OTU-to-Genus mapping
  taxonomy <- as.data.frame(tax_table(Protein_filt))  # Replace `Protein_filt` with your phyloseq object
  taxonomy <- taxonomy %>%
    tibble::rownames_to_column(var = "OTU") %>%   # Move OTU IDs to a column
    replace_na(list(Genus = "Unknown"))           # Replace NA genus names with "Unknown"

  # Create a mapping of OTU to Genus
  otu_to_genus <- taxonomy$Genus
  names(otu_to_genus) <- taxonomy$OTU

  # Replace OTU IDs in matrices with Genus names
  rownames(cor_matrix_top50) <- otu_to_genus[rownames(cor_matrix_top50)]
  rownames(significant_markers_top50) <- otu_to_genus[rownames(significant_markers_top50)]

  # Remove rows with NA or "Unknown" Genus names
  cor_matrix_top50 <- cor_matrix_top50[!is.na(rownames(cor_matrix_top50)) & rownames(cor_matrix_top50) != "Unknown", ]
  significant_markers_top50 <- significant_markers_top50[!is.na(rownames(significant_markers_top50)) & rownames(significant_markers_top50) != "Unknown", ]

  # Ensure both matrices have aligned rows
  common_rows <- intersect(rownames(cor_matrix_top50), rownames(significant_markers_top50))
  cor_matrix_top50 <- cor_matrix_top50[common_rows, , drop = FALSE]
  significant_markers_top50 <- significant_markers_top50[common_rows, , drop = FALSE]

  # Save the updated matrices
  saveRDS(cor_matrix_top50, updated_cor_matrix_file)
  saveRDS(significant_markers_top50, updated_significant_markers_file)
  cat("Updated matrices saved.\n")
} else {
  # Load previously saved matrices
  cor_matrix_top50 <- readRDS(updated_cor_matrix_file)
  significant_markers_top50 <- readRDS(updated_significant_markers_file)
  cat("Updated matrices loaded from saved files.\n")
}
